---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service - ToolVerse"
  description="Terms of service details for ToolVerse. All tools are offered free of charge and as-is under open source conditions."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto glass-card p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-3xl space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-text-main border-b border-border-card pb-3">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-text-muted">Last Updated: July 3, 2026</p>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-text-main">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        By accessing and using ToolVerse.com, you agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, please do not use our utilities.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-text-main">2. Permitted Use</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        You may use ToolVerse's tools for personal, academic, or professional engineering activities. Since all operations run locally in your browser, you must not use the tools to compile malicious code or distribute illegal contents.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-text-main">3. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        All software code, custom runners, designs and site templates are open-source. You may clone, modify, or deploy ToolVerse privately under the terms of the MIT license.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-text-main">4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
        ToolVerse is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We are not liable for any issues, data errors, compilation failures, or code generation bugs resulting from the use of our web services.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
